ostcritically finite parameters, proving the dynamical André-Oort conjecture for curves in this context, originally stated by Baker and DeMarco.This is a reader-friendly invitation to a new and exciting research area that brings together sophisticated tools from many branches of mathematics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aMATHEMATICS / Geometry / Algebraic.2bisacsh  aAffine plane.  aAffine space.  aAffine transformation.  aAlgebraic closure.  aAlgebraic curve.  aAlgebraic equation.  aAlgebraic extension.  aAlgebraic surface.  aAlgebraic variety.  aAlgebraically closed field.  aAnalysis.  aAnalytic function.  aAnalytic geometry.  aApproximation.  aArithmetic dynamics.  aAsymmetric graph.  aBall (mathematics).  aBifurcation theory.  aBoundary (topology).  aCantor set.  aCharacterization (mathematics).  aChebyshev polynomials.  aCoefficient.  aCombinatorics.  aComplex manifold.  aComplex number.  aComputation.  aComputer programming.  aConjugacy class.  aConnected component (graph theory).  aContinuous function (set theory).  aCoprime integers.  aCorrespondence theorem (group theory).  aCounting.  aCritical graph.  aCubic function.  aDatasheet.  aDisk (mathematics).  aDivisor (algebraic geometry).  aElliptic curve.  aEquation.  aEquidistribution theorem.  aEquivalence relation.  aEuclidean topology.  aExistential quantification.  aFixed point (mathematics).  aFunction space.  aGeometric (company).  aGraph (discrete mathematics).  aHamiltonian mechanics.  aHausdorff dimension.  aHausdorff measure.  aHolomorphic function.  aInequality (mathematics).  aInstance (computer science).  aInteger.  aIntermediate value theorem.  aIntersection (set theory).  aInverse-square law.  aIrreducible component.  aIterat